######################################### virsion 03

If You’re in a Docker Container
If changes like apt-get install don’t stick (because containers are ephemeral unless committed), here’s what to do:

Exit the Container
Type exit to leave the current container session.
Run a New Container with Interactive Shell
Start your image again with -it to get a shell:
bash

Collapse

Wrap

Copy
docker run -it lvlane_ubuntu_image bash
Install libcrypt-dev Inside
Inside the container:
bash

Collapse

Wrap

Copy
apt-get update && apt-get install -y libcrypt-dev
Build Again
Navigate to /app/LVLane/ and retry:
bash

Collapse

Wrap

Copy
cd /app/LVLane/
python setup.py build
Commit the Changes (Optional)
If this works and you want to save the updated environment:
Find the container ID:
bash

Collapse

Wrap

Copy
docker ps -a
Commit it to a new image:
bash

Collapse

Wrap

Copy
docker commit <container_id> lvlane_ubuntu_image_updated

